#: resources/views/modules/statistics-chart/Templates/Family.phtml:750
msgid ""
"The maximum generation depth is the longest unbroken parent-child chain "
"recorded in the tree. The widget walks every individual upward, follows "
"fathers and mothers in parallel, and reports the deepest verified line. The "
"distribution histogram on the right shows, for every individual, how many "
"generations of descendants sit below them in the tree — so a value of 0 "
"means a leaf (no recorded descendants), and the bucket at the maximum depth "
"shows the eldest ancestors. A safety cap at 20 generations catches "
"accidentally-cyclic GEDCOM edits."
msgstr ""

